questions.questionTitle: Look at your Writing Goals that you set for yourself earlier this year.  Which domain did you choose to focus on?
If you chose Organizing and Elaborating, what steps did you select to reach your goal?
questions.questionOptions: [{"optionText":"replace tired words with more interesting ones","optionTags":"","optionType":"normal"},{"optionText":"organize writing into paragraphs with clear beginning, middle, and end using transitions","optionTags":"","optionType":"normal"},{"optionText":"use descriptive words to create a picture in the reader's mind","optionTags":"","optionType":"normal"},{"optionText":"include examples of figurative language (simile, hyperbole, etc.)","optionTags":"","optionType":"normal"},{"optionText":"evaluate word choice for the meaning or feeling it suggests","optionTags":"","optionType":"normal"},{"optionText":"check that sentences are in order so that the paragraph meaning is clear","optionTags":"","optionType":"normal"}]

questions.questionTitle: If you chose Capitalization/Spelling/Punctuation, what steps did you select to reach your goal?
questions.questionOptions: [{"optionText":"make certain that each sentence begins with a capital letter and ends with the correct punctuation","optionTags":"","optionType":"normal"},{"optionText":"during writing, highlight words which you are unsure of how to spell, then, during editing, check the spelling of those words","optionTags":"","optionType":"normal"},{"optionText":"use complete sentences","optionTags":"","optionType":"normal"},{"optionText":"correctly use apostrophes","optionTags":"","optionType":"normal"}]

questions.questionTitle: If you chose Communicating Ideas, what steps did you select to reach your goal?
questions.questionOptions: [{"optionText":"provide examples (details) to support the main idea","optionTags":"","optionType":"normal"},{"optionText":"stay on topic within each paragraph","optionTags":"","optionType":"normal"},{"optionText":"prepare the reader for the next paragraph with a good transition sentence","optionTags":"","optionType":"normal"},{"optionText":"use a variety of pre-writing strategies","optionTags":"","optionType":"normal"},{"optionText":"format writing to specific topic and purpose","optionTags":"","optionType":"normal"},{"optionText":"use a web or list to plan writing","optionTags":"","optionType":"normal"},{"optionText":"make certain that each paragraph has a topic sentence and at least three sentences that explain the topic sentence","optionTags":"","optionType":"normal"},{"optionText":"think about the audience when planning and writing","optionTags":"","optionType":"normal"}]

questions.questionTitle: If you chose Grammar/Structure/Paragraphs, what steps did you select to reach your goal?
questions.questionOptions: [{"optionText":"limit the use of the word \"and\" to once per sentence at most","optionTags":"","optionType":"normal"},{"optionText":"make certain each sentence in a paragraph supports the main idea","optionTags":"","optionType":"normal"},{"optionText":"make certain that each paragraph has a topic sentence and at least three sentences that explain the topic sentence","optionTags":"","optionType":"normal"},{"optionText":"make certain that each sentence in a paragraph begins differently","optionTags":"","optionType":"normal"},{"optionText":"revise writing by combining short sentences","optionTags":"","optionType":"normal"},{"optionText":"make certain that you use complete and correct sentences","optionTags":"","optionType":"normal"}]
